dvisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Spring Test's published artifact only brings in spring-core, but its normal TestContext/AOT APIs and existing meaningful tests use Spring ApplicationContext types from spring-context.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework:spring-context:7.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"spring-test declares spring-context as optional in the Spring Framework build, while core TestContext classes such as MergedContextConfiguration, TestContextManager, AotContextLoader, and the existing tests use org.springframework.context APIs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment variable is indicated. Keep tests in-memory with GenericApplicationContext or similar Spring context types. If adapting the existing AOT resource-hint test, Spring 7 registers web resource base path directory patterns with '**' rather than the older '*' expectation.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-test has many optional integration surfaces; tests that choose servlet mocks, MockMvc, WebFlux, JDBC, Mockito, TestNG, or HtmlUnit may need additional optional dependencies, but those are not required for the existing TestContext/AOT coverage path.\",\n    \"The reported failure appears to be an assertion drift across Spring 6 to 7 rather than missing runtime infrastructure; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a3bd4cce993e040016a28a3b4b18c81909e270ab2ba3c23e3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1756, "output": 823, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40979, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781048231522, "responseId": "resp_0a3bd4cce993e040016a28a3a868248190bacd1dd945581a71"}}
